WEBVTT

1
00:02:25.355 --> 00:02:27.815
<i>Duty is sacrifice.</i>

2
00:02:29.442 --> 00:02:31.194
<i>It eclipses all things...</i>

3
00:02:31.944 --> 00:02:32.945
<i>even blood.</i>

4
00:02:35.281 --> 00:02:37.950
<i>All men of honor
must pay its price.</i>

5
00:02:43.039 --> 00:02:46.042
<i>The North owes a great duty
to the Seven Kingdoms...</i>

6
00:02:46.709 --> 00:02:49.379
<i>one older than any oath.</i>

7
00:02:50.046 --> 00:02:51.839
<i>Since the days of the First Men.</i>

8
00:02:51.923 --> 00:02:55.551
<i>we have stood as guardians
against the cold and the dark.</i>

9
00:02:57.261 --> 00:02:58.888
<i>Through its long tradition.</i>

10
00:02:58.971 --> 00:03:02.225
<i>the Night's Watch cultivated its strength
from doomed men</i>

11
00:03:02.308 --> 00:03:04.769
<i>who had their life
as their only possession.</i>

12
00:03:05.436 --> 00:03:08.189
<i>But my ancestor. Torrhen Stark.</i>

13
00:03:08.272 --> 00:03:11.943
<i>began a tradition by making an offering
at the onset of winter:</i>

14
00:03:12.819 --> 00:03:18.116
<i>One in ten men from our household
was to be chosen to fortify the Watch.</i>

15
00:03:20.993 --> 00:03:24.122
<i>This is not a sentence</i>

16
00:03:24.205 --> 00:03:25.415
<i>but an honor.</i>

17
00:03:26.332 --> 00:03:29.627
<i>A duty embraced by all
who serve the North.</i>

18
00:03:30.503 --> 00:03:32.338
<i>Even by mine own kin.</i>

19
00:03:37.802 --> 00:03:39.804
<i>The North must stand ready.</i>

20
00:03:41.681 --> 00:03:43.307
<i>Winter is coming.</i>

21
00:03:43.391 --> 00:03:44.434
Coming?

22
00:03:44.517 --> 00:03:47.520
What is this. then. that falls from
the skies and shivers my bones?

23
00:03:47.603 --> 00:03:50.481
This is only a late summer snow.
my prince.

24
00:03:51.274 --> 00:03:53.317
In winter. it will cover all you see.

25
00:03:53.860 --> 00:03:56.154
And all memories of warmth
will be forgotten.

26
00:03:57.363 --> 00:03:59.574
It pleases me to think that.
over a century ago.

27
00:03:59.657 --> 00:04:02.034
our ancestors treated in this very place.

28
00:04:03.661 --> 00:04:05.496
The Conqueror and the King in the North.

29
00:04:07.373 --> 00:04:11.419
You. at least. have the mercy
not to threaten me with your dragon.

30
00:04:19.677 --> 00:04:20.678
My prince.

31
00:04:21.471 --> 00:04:22.513
My lord.

32
00:04:22.597 --> 00:04:23.598
My lord.

33
00:04:24.682 --> 00:04:25.808
My lord.

34
00:04:25.892 --> 00:04:30.062
Surely the great Torrhen Stark
would have sooner died than bent the knee.

35
00:04:31.063 --> 00:04:34.484
Unless he believed the Conqueror
could bring unity to the Seven Kingdoms.

36
00:04:35.860 --> 00:04:39.530
- You are right in that.
- That unity is now threatened.

37
00:04:40.698 --> 00:04:42.658
The realm will soon tear itself apart...

38
00:04:43.451 --> 00:04:48.122
if men do not remember the oaths sworn
to King Viserys and to his rightful heir.

39
00:04:48.789 --> 00:04:52.043
Starks do not forget their oaths.
my prince.

40
00:04:52.835 --> 00:04:57.423
But you must know that my gaze
is forever torn between north and south.

41
00:04:58.716 --> 00:05:01.928
In winter. my duty to the Wall
is even more dire

42
00:05:02.011 --> 00:05:03.846
than the one I owe to King's Landing.

43
00:05:03.930 --> 00:05:05.556
I need my men here.

44
00:05:06.182 --> 00:05:09.101
Whilst your men guard
against wildlings and weather.

45
00:05:09.185 --> 00:05:11.812
the Hightowers plan to usurp the throne.

46
00:05:12.772 --> 00:05:14.732
If my mother is to defend her claim.

47
00:05:14.815 --> 00:05:18.486
to hold the realm united.
she needs an army. War is coming.

48
00:05:18.569 --> 00:05:20.655
To the whole of the realm. my lord.

49
00:05:20.738 --> 00:05:23.115
We cannot wage it
without the support of the North.

50
00:05:31.541 --> 00:05:35.586
My father brought King Jaehaerys
and Queen Alysanne to see the Wall.

51
00:05:36.087 --> 00:05:39.173
His Grace stood at this very outlook

52
00:05:39.257 --> 00:05:41.217
and watched as their dragons.

53
00:05:41.300 --> 00:05:45.346
the greatest power in the world.
refused to cross it.

54
00:05:47.598 --> 00:05:51.394
Do you think my ancestors built
a 700-foot wall of ice

55
00:05:51.477 --> 00:05:53.646
to keep out snow and savages?

56
00:05:54.522 --> 00:05:55.898
What does it keep out?

57
00:05:58.359 --> 00:05:59.360
Death.

58
00:06:07.785 --> 00:06:11.956
I have thousands of graybeards
who have already seen too many winters.

59
00:06:12.748 --> 00:06:15.126
They are well-honed.

60
00:06:15.918 --> 00:06:16.919
So they're old.

61
00:06:18.421 --> 00:06:20.423
I can ready them to march at once.

62
00:06:21.340 --> 00:06:23.926
If your graybeards can fight.
the queen will have them.

63
00:06:24.927 --> 00:06:26.762
They will fight hard.

64
00:06:26.846 --> 00:06:28.514
Like Northerners.

65
00:06:28.598 --> 00:06:29.724
My lord.

66
00:06:31.434 --> 00:06:34.854
A raven's arrived.
Urgent news from Dragonstone.

67
00:07:08.596 --> 00:07:10.014
<i>Gevi.</i> Meleys.

68
00:07:17.021 --> 00:07:18.661
Take your mount again.

69
00:07:19.649 --> 00:07:20.733
We're flying out.

70
00:07:23.402 --> 00:07:27.948
I alone patrol over a hundred miles
of open sea. endlessly.

71
00:07:28.032 --> 00:07:29.367
to hold the blockade.

72
00:07:30.868 --> 00:07:34.121
Meleys must gorge and rest. As must I.

73
00:07:35.873 --> 00:07:38.250
- We're going to King's Landing.
- To what end?

74
00:07:38.334 --> 00:07:39.835
Killing Vhagar.

75
00:07:39.919 --> 00:07:42.254
I cannot face
that hoary. old bitch alone...

76
00:07:43.089 --> 00:07:47.093
but with my dragon and yours together.
we can kill Vhagar and her rider.

77
00:07:47.176 --> 00:07:48.427
Make it a son for a son.

78
00:07:50.680 --> 00:07:53.432
- Was this the queen's command?
- The queen remains absent.

79
00:07:53.516 --> 00:07:55.518
I should be at Harrenhal. bending knees.

80
00:07:55.601 --> 00:07:58.104
but I must instead remain here
to wage her war.

81
00:07:58.187 --> 00:08:00.940
Or perhaps more simply.
to await her return.

82
00:08:01.023 --> 00:08:04.276
She has been gone for days.
Too long. She is exposed.

83
00:08:04.360 --> 00:08:05.778
She is grieving.

84
00:08:05.861 --> 00:08:08.989
The mother grieves
as the queen shirks her duties.

85
00:08:10.866 --> 00:08:14.161
It was a raven that brought me news
of Laena's death.

86
00:08:15.204 --> 00:08:17.331
I existed for weeks in torment...

87
00:08:18.457 --> 00:08:20.584
refusing to believe what I'd been told.

88
00:08:23.379 --> 00:08:26.173
It was only when I saw
my daughter's mortal remains

89
00:08:26.257 --> 00:08:28.050
that I could begin to mourn her.

90
00:08:30.720 --> 00:08:34.223
A raven has told Rhaenyra
that her son is dead.

91
00:08:35.391 --> 00:08:38.811
- She needs to know it for certain.
- She was a fool to go alone.

92
00:08:40.146 --> 00:08:43.524
- What if Aemond were to happen upon her?
- Then I would pity Aemond.

93
00:08:46.152 --> 00:08:48.195
The queen was wise to recuse herself.

94
00:08:49.363 --> 00:08:52.867
She has not acted on the vengeful impulse
that others might have.

95
00:08:54.827 --> 00:08:57.288
If you'd have acted
when you had the chance...

96
00:08:58.164 --> 00:09:00.124
Aegon's line would be extinguished...

97
00:09:02.001 --> 00:09:03.544
and Luke would be alive.

98
00:09:11.427 --> 00:09:12.636
Fly with me.

99
00:09:13.846 --> 00:09:15.222
It is a command.

100
00:09:15.306 --> 00:09:17.057
Would that you were the king.

101
00:10:08.943 --> 00:10:10.236
- My lord.
- My lord.

102
00:10:10.319 --> 00:10:11.612
- My lord.
- My lord.

103
00:10:11.695 --> 00:10:13.280
- My lord.
- My lord.

104
00:10:18.577 --> 00:10:19.578
My lord.

105
00:10:27.419 --> 00:10:28.420
My lord.

106
00:10:31.382 --> 00:10:34.426
It's a marvel she was able to return
from the Stepstones at all.

107
00:10:36.804 --> 00:10:38.138
Barely done but done.

108
00:10:39.056 --> 00:10:42.268
Seven more ships put out to sea this morn
to fortify the blockade.

109
00:10:42.852 --> 00:10:45.312
The Gullet is vast and we are not like
to have the numbers

110
00:10:45.396 --> 00:10:46.814
to cover all that open water.

111
00:10:50.276 --> 00:10:53.320
I must have my ship
back at sea. to lead the effort.

112
00:10:53.404 --> 00:10:55.614
It'll be many weeks yet. I'd wager.

113
00:10:58.117 --> 00:10:59.994
But I'll have a word with my brother...

114
00:11:00.494 --> 00:11:02.830
to see what reinforcements
the shipwrights can muster.

115
00:11:13.632 --> 00:11:16.218
The smithy delivered this earlier.

116
00:11:18.387 --> 00:11:19.388
My lord?

117
00:11:28.314 --> 00:11:30.858
I had this commissioned
for Prince Lucerys.

118
00:11:33.611 --> 00:11:36.071
I was very sorry to hear about
your heir's death.

119
00:11:37.156 --> 00:11:38.699
'Twas the blackest of treacheries.

120
00:11:42.411 --> 00:11:43.954
Pardon. my lord.

121
00:11:44.038 --> 00:11:46.457
If it'll please you. Much to do.

122
00:11:47.291 --> 00:11:50.252
They tell me that you are the one
that dragged my body out of the sea.

123
00:11:55.966 --> 00:11:57.217
It was only my duty.

124
00:12:02.139 --> 00:12:04.808
I am indebted to you. Alyn.

125
00:12:42.638 --> 00:12:44.616
- To attention. men!
- On your feet!

126
00:12:44.640 --> 00:12:47.768
- Mind your posts.
- To your stations!

127
00:12:49.436 --> 00:12:50.980
Keep your focus. men!

128
00:12:55.025 --> 00:12:57.528
- Dragon!
- Dragon!

129
00:12:57.611 --> 00:13:00.739
- Arm the scorpion!
- Arm the scorpion!

130
00:13:03.409 --> 00:13:05.619
Approaching from the southeast!

131
00:13:05.703 --> 00:13:06.954
Bring it around!

132
00:13:11.291 --> 00:13:14.044
- Scorpion ready!
- Hold!

133
00:13:14.628 --> 00:13:15.629
Hold!

134
00:13:18.132 --> 00:13:19.591
Stand down! It's Vhagar.

135
00:13:20.217 --> 00:13:23.053
- Stand down!
- Standing down!

136
00:13:50.414 --> 00:13:51.415
Where is Jaehaerys?

137
00:13:53.500 --> 00:13:55.127
Attending his lessons.

138
00:13:56.295 --> 00:13:57.337
And those are where?

139
00:13:58.088 --> 00:13:59.465
What do you need of him?

140
00:13:59.548 --> 00:14:01.008
Taking him to the small council.

141
00:14:01.675 --> 00:14:03.886
He'll be king one day.
He must begin his instruction.

142
00:14:05.220 --> 00:14:06.972
What if he does not want to be king?

143
00:14:08.474 --> 00:14:10.851
- Where is he?
- The library.

144
00:14:11.477 --> 00:14:13.228
You must not interrupt his custom.

145
00:14:20.569 --> 00:14:21.653
I'm afraid.

146
00:14:24.615 --> 00:14:25.616
Don't be.

147
00:14:26.492 --> 00:14:28.869
They'd be fools to come
with Vhagar protecting the city.

148
00:14:28.952 --> 00:14:30.454
Not the dragons.

149
00:14:32.122 --> 00:14:33.123
The rats.

150
00:14:42.382 --> 00:14:44.301
The queen is an enduring mystery...

151
00:14:45.511 --> 00:14:46.595
is she not?

152
00:15:20.921 --> 00:15:22.589
There's a chill in the air.

153
00:15:26.969 --> 00:15:28.595
Summer is well and truly through.

154
00:15:30.556 --> 00:15:32.975
We are expected
at the small council. Your Grace.

155
00:15:49.074 --> 00:15:50.200
We cannot...

156
00:15:51.201 --> 00:15:52.202
again.

157
00:15:55.455 --> 00:15:56.582
Yes. Your Grace.

158
00:16:01.795 --> 00:16:02.921
If you wouldn't mind?

159
00:16:36.955 --> 00:16:38.373
- Your Grace.
- Good day.

160
00:16:44.129 --> 00:16:46.065
Jaehaerys must learn
the ways of the court

161
00:16:46.089 --> 00:16:48.759
if he is to rule one day.
Up we go.

162
00:16:49.593 --> 00:16:53.096
Good morrow. my lords!

163
00:16:53.764 --> 00:16:54.765
Mother.

164
00:16:57.059 --> 00:16:58.685
What news?

165
00:16:58.769 --> 00:17:02.981
Our letters to the Vale and
to the North continue to go unanswered.

166
00:17:04.066 --> 00:17:05.067
Cunts.

167
00:17:06.777 --> 00:17:09.071
The Stormlands should be ours

168
00:17:09.154 --> 00:17:13.033
after Prince Aemond's marriage pact
to the Lady Floris Baratheon.

169
00:17:13.116 --> 00:17:15.577
I anticipate their sworn declaration.

170
00:17:16.286 --> 00:17:19.331
My brother is raising
the strength of the West

171
00:17:19.414 --> 00:17:21.750
to mass at the Golden Tooth. but we...

172
00:17:22.584 --> 00:17:25.921
Ye... Thank you. my prince.
That's... That's very helpful.

173
00:17:26.588 --> 00:17:31.343
My nephew. Lord Ormund. musters his forces
to sally forth from Oldtown.

174
00:17:31.426 --> 00:17:33.971
They expect to march quickly.
meeting little resistance.

175
00:17:34.054 --> 00:17:36.473
until they reach the Riverlands.

176
00:17:36.556 --> 00:17:38.976
My letters to Rhaenyra.
has there been any answer?

177
00:17:39.059 --> 00:17:42.604
- An apology for her dead son?
- None. Your Grace.

178
00:17:42.688 --> 00:17:44.940
Between that
and their blockade of the Gullet.

179
00:17:45.023 --> 00:17:48.443
we must presume that the princess
has refused the offered terms.

180
00:17:48.527 --> 00:17:51.071
And that war is now inevitable.

181
00:17:51.905 --> 00:17:54.533
Perhaps Your Grace might
lend his voice to our outreach...

182
00:17:54.616 --> 00:17:56.034
Stop! Enough.

183
00:17:56.118 --> 00:17:58.495
...in hopes that new terms
might be negotiated.

184
00:17:58.578 --> 00:18:01.415
Release it at once.
Would someone please...?

185
00:18:01.498 --> 00:18:03.709
Is the heir to the throne
bothering you. Tyland?

186
00:18:05.794 --> 00:18:09.506
No. No. no. not in the least. Your Grace.

187
00:18:09.589 --> 00:18:11.383
Because... I think he wants a ride.

188
00:18:12.009 --> 00:18:13.278
- Your Grace.
- A ride?

189
00:18:13.302 --> 00:18:14.720
A pony ride.

190
00:18:15.345 --> 00:18:16.763
Wouldn't that be fun. Jaehaerys?

191
00:18:16.847 --> 00:18:19.766
Should the Master of Coin
be your royal steed?

192
00:18:27.983 --> 00:18:28.984
Your Grace.

193
00:18:30.402 --> 00:18:32.529
There are important matters to discuss.

194
00:18:33.989 --> 00:18:35.782
Despite Sir Tyland's interruptions.

195
00:18:37.284 --> 00:18:38.285
Very well.

196
00:18:39.536 --> 00:18:41.455
No time for amusements. Tyland.

197
00:18:43.373 --> 00:18:44.374
Your Grace.

198
00:18:45.625 --> 00:18:47.586
Off you go. Jaehaerys. Good boy.

199
00:18:50.672 --> 00:18:52.174
Where were we?

200
00:18:53.675 --> 00:18:57.679
Rhaenyra's blockade has placed
King's Landing under strain

201
00:18:57.763 --> 00:19:00.223
and those pressures will multiply quickly.

202
00:19:00.307 --> 00:19:02.934
We should have just killed her
when we had the chance.

203
00:19:03.018 --> 00:19:05.562
Regrettably. the opportunity for surprise
has been lost.

204
00:19:06.146 --> 00:19:09.274
And with it.
the chance to end this conflict quickly.

205
00:19:11.151 --> 00:19:13.195
We must play the board before us.

206
00:19:13.278 --> 00:19:15.906
If we are to break
the Sea Snake's blockade.

207
00:19:15.989 --> 00:19:19.201
we will need to bolster both
the Lannister and Hightower navies.

208
00:19:19.284 --> 00:19:21.286
We do have need for a new Master of Ships.

209
00:19:21.912 --> 00:19:24.664
We could offer the title
to the young Lord Dalton Greyjoy.

210
00:19:24.748 --> 00:19:28.126
- Aemond. What is your business here?
- The king summoned me.

211
00:19:28.210 --> 00:19:29.920
You do not have a seat at this council.

212
00:19:30.003 --> 00:19:34.216
Aemond is my closest blood
and our best sword. I welcome him.

213
00:19:35.425 --> 00:19:38.303
The path to King's Landing
is through the Riverlands.

214
00:19:38.387 --> 00:19:41.973
We must establish a toehold there.
at Harrenhal.

215
00:19:42.057 --> 00:19:44.059
The Riverlords
will either declare for me.

216
00:19:44.142 --> 00:19:47.062
or they will meet Vhagar
and Sunfyre together.

217
00:19:47.145 --> 00:19:49.189
And we can burn the blockade
while we're at it.

218
00:19:49.272 --> 00:19:50.565
Rhaenyra has dragons as well.

219
00:19:50.649 --> 00:19:52.901
- Mine are bigger.
- If we loose the dragons to war.

220
00:19:52.984 --> 00:19:55.529
there will be no calling them back.
We must proceed cautiously.

221
00:19:55.612 --> 00:19:59.574
Fat. old Lord Tully will either
raise my banner or see his burn.

222
00:19:59.658 --> 00:20:01.034
We should fly to Riverrun.

223
00:20:02.285 --> 00:20:05.247
You are the king. Your Grace.
You must not put yourself at risk.

224
00:20:05.330 --> 00:20:06.665
And Vhagar is needed here.

225
00:20:06.748 --> 00:20:10.669
to deter Rhaenyra from attacking
in retribution for the death of her son.

226
00:20:11.711 --> 00:20:16.091
Errors were made in the hours
following King Viserys's death.

227
00:20:16.174 --> 00:20:18.218
We mustn't compound them.

228
00:20:19.928 --> 00:20:22.472
You've already demonstrated
your might. Your Grace.

229
00:20:22.556 --> 00:20:26.101
We must now favor patience and restraint.

230
00:20:26.935 --> 00:20:28.770
I send ravens by the hour.

231
00:20:28.854 --> 00:20:33.066
Many and more houses
will declare for you in time.

232
00:20:33.150 --> 00:20:36.153
History and precedent
will come to your side.

233
00:20:44.035 --> 00:20:46.621
- Good morrow. Your Grace.
- Good morrow. Lord Larys.

234
00:20:47.414 --> 00:20:50.542
I had come earlier to have a word
before the small council convened.

235
00:20:50.625 --> 00:20:54.588
but your handmaiden said
that you were indisposed?

236
00:20:58.425 --> 00:20:59.885
What is it you wish to discuss?

237
00:21:02.554 --> 00:21:05.599
I have completed questioning
the whole of the castle staff.

238
00:21:07.100 --> 00:21:08.977
They produced rather interesting details.

239
00:21:09.060 --> 00:21:13.106
but I am satisfied I have exposed
all who betrayed our trust.

240
00:21:15.567 --> 00:21:16.651
And what of them?

241
00:21:18.153 --> 00:21:20.113
They no longer breathe our air.

242
00:21:22.532 --> 00:21:25.410
I have chosen your new staff personally.

243
00:21:44.638 --> 00:21:46.181
Just... Give me that.

244
00:21:46.973 --> 00:21:48.141
Your Grace?

245
00:21:49.184 --> 00:21:50.268
Just leave me.

246
00:21:52.687 --> 00:21:54.523
Just... Just leave me.

247
00:22:37.357 --> 00:22:39.776
- It's a dragon wing!
- Let's have a look!

248
00:22:41.444 --> 00:22:43.564
- It's a wing.
- Who cares what it is.

249
00:22:44.072 --> 00:22:45.657
D rag o n!

250
00:24:12.494 --> 00:24:14.996
All hail King Aegon!

251
00:24:15.580 --> 00:24:19.834
Aegon the Magnanimous.
Second of His Name.

252
00:24:19.918 --> 00:24:23.213
King of the Andals. and the Rhoynar.
and the First Men.

253
00:24:23.296 --> 00:24:26.424
Lord of the Seven Kingdoms
and Protector of the Realm.

254
00:24:26.508 --> 00:24:28.134
Hail King Aegon!

255
00:24:29.094 --> 00:24:30.553
"The Magnanimous"?

256
00:24:34.557 --> 00:24:35.642
Your Grace.

257
00:24:36.351 --> 00:24:39.396
Let's have the first petition.
my good Lord Hand.

258
00:24:43.858 --> 00:24:45.694
Good morrow. my. uh. Your Grace.

259
00:24:45.777 --> 00:24:49.030
It's all right.
There's no reason to be nervous.

260
00:24:49.114 --> 00:24:50.323
What's your name?

261
00:24:50.407 --> 00:24:52.575
Jerard. Your Grace.

262
00:24:52.659 --> 00:24:54.160
Good morrow. Jerard.

263
00:24:54.703 --> 00:24:56.788
And how might your king be of service?

264
00:24:57.455 --> 00:24:58.957
'Tis my flock.

265
00:25:00.125 --> 00:25:03.253
A tenth of them taken by...

266
00:25:05.588 --> 00:25:10.051
the Crown on the cusp of winter.

267
00:25:10.885 --> 00:25:13.763
- If I'd had the time to plan. perhaps...
- We should return them.

268
00:25:16.850 --> 00:25:18.351
Your Grace?

269
00:25:18.435 --> 00:25:20.603
You need your goats
for the winter. don't you?

270
00:25:20.687 --> 00:25:22.856
- Sheep. Your Grace.
- Sheep. even better.

271
00:25:22.939 --> 00:25:25.233
I shall make your flock of sheep whole.

272
00:25:26.985 --> 00:25:29.487
We already made a promise
to all the Crownlands

273
00:25:29.571 --> 00:25:34.200
that a tithing of livestock
would be necessary to sustain the dragons

274
00:25:34.284 --> 00:25:38.371
for their increased activity
and. pray not. eventual fighting.

275
00:25:39.289 --> 00:25:41.458
Right. Right.

276
00:25:41.541 --> 00:25:44.544
Perhaps we could just return his sheep?
He came all this way.

277
00:25:44.627 --> 00:25:47.297
If you return one herder's sheep.
Your Grace.

278
00:25:47.380 --> 00:25:51.384
you'll soon find them all at the foot
of your throne expecting the same.

279
00:25:52.135 --> 00:25:53.595
They won't know.

280
00:25:53.678 --> 00:25:57.557
When the king speaks. Your Grace.

281
00:25:57.640 --> 00:25:59.517
all hear it.

282
00:26:08.318 --> 00:26:10.403
After further thought.

283
00:26:10.487 --> 00:26:13.782
I have decided
that I cannot restore your sheep.

284
00:26:13.865 --> 00:26:17.035
If war were to break out.
my dragons will require feed.

285
00:26:17.118 --> 00:26:18.620
- Bring the next.
- But...

286
00:26:19.913 --> 00:26:24.167
Salts always run scarce
on the road to winter. Your Grace.

287
00:26:24.250 --> 00:26:27.962
We rely on ships from Essos
for our supply.

288
00:26:28.046 --> 00:26:31.466
But now. with a blockade in place
and war threatening...

289
00:26:31.549 --> 00:26:35.678
That treasonous blockade won't last long.
I plan to send Vhagar to burn it to ash.

290
00:26:35.762 --> 00:26:37.096
Bring the next.

291
00:26:41.142 --> 00:26:42.435
Hugh. Your Grace.

292
00:26:46.189 --> 00:26:49.734
The smiths are all proud
to support Your Grace against Rhaenyra.

293
00:26:53.696 --> 00:26:55.532
- But?
- But...

294
00:26:57.617 --> 00:26:59.410
iron costs have grown.

295
00:27:00.578 --> 00:27:03.456
A lone scorpion takes weeks to build.

296
00:27:04.791 --> 00:27:06.459
To put it simply. we are struggling.

297
00:27:07.877 --> 00:27:12.298
If we could but have the Crown's coin
before we started work.

298
00:27:12.382 --> 00:27:14.300
it would bring great relief.

299
00:27:14.384 --> 00:27:17.637
Not just to me
but to all the smiths serving your cause.

300
00:27:22.225 --> 00:27:24.853
You shall be paid and paid well.

301
00:27:25.687 --> 00:27:28.064
My army cannot win a war
without your weapons.

302
00:27:28.147 --> 00:27:29.899
You should continue their making.

303
00:27:30.567 --> 00:27:34.153
Our victory depends
on the efforts of the smallfolk.

304
00:27:36.573 --> 00:27:38.825
You have my most sincere gratitude.
Your Grace.

305
00:27:39.742 --> 00:27:41.536
I'll hear the next petition.

306
00:27:49.335 --> 00:27:52.255
Your Grace. it filled my heart
to see you on the Iron Throne.

307
00:27:52.881 --> 00:27:55.466
I was only a boy when Jaehaerys
last graced the seat.

308
00:27:55.550 --> 00:27:57.218
but you brought forth memories of him.

309
00:27:57.302 --> 00:28:00.805
You have such a deft touch with
the smallfolk. just as your father did.

310
00:28:00.889 --> 00:28:02.056
Thank you. my lord.

311
00:28:02.724 --> 00:28:04.726
I wonder. do you have a moment
for a quiet word?

312
00:28:11.107 --> 00:28:14.611
It is the Hand's wont
to keep a firm grip on things.

313
00:28:14.694 --> 00:28:15.694
Mm.

314
00:28:16.279 --> 00:28:18.406
He controlled your father the same way.

315
00:28:20.450 --> 00:28:23.119
Viserys had a certain reputation
as being pliable.

316
00:28:23.202 --> 00:28:24.245
I am aware.

317
00:28:26.247 --> 00:28:30.752
I would think. as we find ourselves
standing within a hair's breadth of war.

318
00:28:30.835 --> 00:28:33.671
that you would wish
to be viewed differently.

319
00:28:36.883 --> 00:28:37.884
How?

320
00:28:38.426 --> 00:28:39.844
Otto Hightower...

321
00:28:41.471 --> 00:28:44.265
was your father's Hand. Your Grace.

322
00:29:01.032 --> 00:29:02.033
Daughter.

323
00:29:03.534 --> 00:29:05.536
I requested an audience hours ago.

324
00:29:07.497 --> 00:29:11.209
There were many petitions.

325
00:29:13.795 --> 00:29:15.380
I find myself wondering...

326
00:29:16.798 --> 00:29:18.341
do we pursue the same end?

327
00:29:20.802 --> 00:29:24.180
I must admit. there are days
where I myself can't be sure.

328
00:29:25.890 --> 00:29:27.225
I shall tell you mine.

329
00:29:29.602 --> 00:29:33.272
- It's victory.
- And how would you define victory?

330
00:29:34.023 --> 00:29:35.817
Rhaenyra bending the knee

331
00:29:35.900 --> 00:29:38.486
and Aegon sitting the Iron Throne
in peace.

332
00:29:39.362 --> 00:29:40.780
As Viserys wished.

333
00:29:40.863 --> 00:29:43.992
If that's how you describe it.
then we are aligned.

334
00:29:44.534 --> 00:29:46.577
- Then be my ally.
- I am.

335
00:29:46.661 --> 00:29:50.498
An ally would not repeatedly cut my legs
from beneath me at that table of men.

336
00:29:50.581 --> 00:29:53.876
- I sit there and I feel your anger.
- Frustration.

337
00:29:53.960 --> 00:29:57.588
These critical days since
Viserys's passing haven't gone to plan.

338
00:29:57.672 --> 00:29:58.673
That's not my fault.

339
00:30:00.633 --> 00:30:05.179
My sons both see you as the great example.
The Hand to three kings.

340
00:30:06.973 --> 00:30:09.892
Aegon is ever eager to prove himself.
and Aemond...

341
00:30:11.769 --> 00:30:13.021
Aemond is angry.

342
00:30:14.939 --> 00:30:17.775
Rhaenyra's son took his eye
and was never punished for it.

343
00:30:17.859 --> 00:30:21.904
- What he did. however vicious...
- The caprice of youth.

344
00:30:26.284 --> 00:30:27.452
I could only hope.

345
00:30:28.202 --> 00:30:30.246
Aemond erred.

346
00:30:31.247 --> 00:30:34.834
But he is fiercely loyal.
He wishes to please.

347
00:30:34.917 --> 00:30:38.129
And Aegon still heeds me.
In private. at least.

348
00:30:39.589 --> 00:30:42.967
But if you undermine my voice.
both those boys will grow deaf to it.

349
00:30:51.434 --> 00:30:53.227
I hadn't seen it that way.

350
00:30:53.853 --> 00:30:57.690
We only need to mind Aegon
until the novelty of rule is spent.

351
00:30:58.983 --> 00:31:02.070
Once he tires of it.
you and I can steer our cause to victory.

352
00:31:02.153 --> 00:31:04.489
A fine strategy. daughter.

353
00:31:05.406 --> 00:31:10.703
But you must accept that the path
to victory now is one of violence.

354
00:31:12.163 --> 00:31:13.164
I know it.

355
00:31:17.418 --> 00:31:19.420
But that does not mean it must be wanton.

356
00:31:22.048 --> 00:31:23.049
No.

357
00:31:39.857 --> 00:31:41.526
Prepare to be boarded!

358
00:31:41.609 --> 00:31:43.027
Boarding party. ready!

359
00:31:43.111 --> 00:31:44.862
Borders inbound!

360
00:31:44.946 --> 00:31:47.740
By the order
of Lord Corlys Velaryon!

361
00:31:47.824 --> 00:31:50.159
Search the hold for stowaways!

362
00:32:05.758 --> 00:32:08.553
Hey! You! What are these?

363
00:32:18.104 --> 00:32:19.105
You.

364
00:32:21.649 --> 00:32:24.277
When last we met. there were two of you.

365
00:32:27.113 --> 00:32:28.573
The White Worm.

366
00:32:28.656 --> 00:32:31.117
Did you think
I would wither in your absence?

367
00:32:31.200 --> 00:32:33.578
I did not think
you would flower a traitor.

368
00:32:33.661 --> 00:32:36.539
You speak of highborn games.
I am common-born.

369
00:32:36.622 --> 00:32:39.083
How long have you been selling secrets
to Otto Hightower?

370
00:32:39.167 --> 00:32:41.169
As long as he had gold to pay for them.

371
00:32:43.713 --> 00:32:47.758
Who sent you fleeing from King's Landing
in such disrepair. hm?

372
00:32:49.302 --> 00:32:51.304
You put Aegon on the throne.

373
00:32:51.387 --> 00:32:53.514
That was the Hightowers' conspiracy.

374
00:32:53.598 --> 00:32:55.975
I merely profited
from knowing Aegon's movements.

375
00:32:56.058 --> 00:32:57.518
But you delivered him.

376
00:32:57.602 --> 00:33:00.396
He would have returned home eventually
for gold and for respite.

377
00:33:00.479 --> 00:33:02.356
as he always does. I simply...

378
00:33:03.065 --> 00:33:05.526
- Simply sped the business along.
- Business that ended

379
00:33:05.610 --> 00:33:08.046
with the theft of the queen's throne
and the murder of her son.

380
00:33:08.070 --> 00:33:10.823
You only blame me because
your true enemies are out of reach.

381
00:33:13.326 --> 00:33:16.245
My arrangement with the Hand
was purely transactional.

382
00:33:16.329 --> 00:33:18.289
I held no loyalty to him.

383
00:33:18.956 --> 00:33:20.499
Certainly do not now.

384
00:33:21.083 --> 00:33:24.545
Otto Hightower was to me
as I am to your noble ilk:

385
00:33:24.629 --> 00:33:26.172
Fodder to be cast off.

386
00:33:26.255 --> 00:33:29.133
- What else do you know of him? His plans?
- Little and less.

387
00:33:32.720 --> 00:33:35.389
I possess nothing of value to you. Daemon.

388
00:33:58.913 --> 00:34:00.456
Have her moved to the cells.

389
00:34:00.539 --> 00:34:02.959
She is to be treated
as a traitor to the crown.

390
00:34:05.878 --> 00:34:09.465
Forgive me. my prince.
but the lady speaks the truth.

391
00:34:09.548 --> 00:34:12.218
- She was no agent of the Hightowers.
- What is it to you?

392
00:34:13.261 --> 00:34:14.387
A matter of honor.

393
00:34:14.470 --> 00:34:16.389
Was it honor
that made you stand by and watch

394
00:34:16.472 --> 00:34:18.224
as the Hightowers usurped the throne?

395
00:34:18.849 --> 00:34:20.601
You and your traitorous twin?

396
00:34:21.435 --> 00:34:22.895
No. my prince.

397
00:34:24.730 --> 00:34:25.731
I'm shamed by it.

398
00:34:26.774 --> 00:34:30.987
That's why I abandoned the Kingsguard
and my brother. and came here.

399
00:34:31.070 --> 00:34:32.280
I don't care.

400
00:34:33.531 --> 00:34:36.450
Aegon was in your grasp.
You should have killed him yourself.

401
00:34:36.534 --> 00:34:39.161
Arryk and I were named to the Kingsguard
at just 8 and 10.

402
00:34:39.996 --> 00:34:41.455
And we swore the same oath:

403
00:34:42.248 --> 00:34:44.083
To defend the whole of the royal family.

404
00:34:45.751 --> 00:34:48.111
So. what were we to do
when they turned against one another?

405
00:35:17.575 --> 00:35:21.912
Queen Rhaenyra Targaryen.
the First of Her Name.

406
00:35:21.996 --> 00:35:23.581
Queen of the Andals.

407
00:35:23.664 --> 00:35:26.334
and the Rhoynar. and the First Men.

408
00:35:26.417 --> 00:35:29.795
Lady of the Seven Kingdoms
and Protector of the Realm.

409
00:35:36.385 --> 00:35:38.137
Did you find what you needed?

410
00:35:47.313 --> 00:35:49.565
Your council stands at the ready.
Your Grace.

411
00:35:54.070 --> 00:35:58.616
I will fly to Harrenhal at your command
and set our toehold in the Riverlands.

412
00:35:59.533 --> 00:36:02.620
Your Grace. my lord husband's blockade
of the Gullet moves into place.

413
00:36:02.703 --> 00:36:05.956
All seaborne travel and trade
to King's Landing will soon be cut off.

414
00:36:12.296 --> 00:36:14.924
I want Aemond Targaryen.

415
00:37:04.014 --> 00:37:06.684
In your years as a merchant of gossip.

416
00:37:06.767 --> 00:37:09.186
you surely accumulated spies
within the Red Keep.

417
00:37:09.270 --> 00:37:11.522
Servants who knew the comings and goings.

418
00:37:11.605 --> 00:37:13.607
Scheme with someone else. Daemon.

419
00:37:13.691 --> 00:37:16.402
I was once in your thrall. But no longer.

420
00:37:18.028 --> 00:37:19.363
A transaction. then.

421
00:37:20.614 --> 00:37:23.159
Your knowledge
in exchange for your freedom.

422
00:37:51.061 --> 00:37:52.062
Your Grace.

423
00:37:56.192 --> 00:37:59.612
Lady Jeyne Arryn has pledged her support

424
00:37:59.695 --> 00:38:02.198
in exchange for a dragon
to guard the Vale.

425
00:38:05.451 --> 00:38:08.204
And Lord Cregan Stark...

426
00:38:11.332 --> 00:38:13.584
has promised 2000 men.

427
00:38:59.505 --> 00:39:00.881
Alyrie Florent.

428
00:39:31.245 --> 00:39:32.788
Viserys Targaryen.

429
00:40:31.138 --> 00:40:32.931
Lucerys Velaryon.

430
00:41:27.528 --> 00:41:28.696
A tribute.

431
00:41:37.705 --> 00:41:38.789
Commander?

432
00:41:39.456 --> 00:41:40.749
Never gone for long.

433
00:41:43.085 --> 00:41:46.213
I'm told you bear a mislike
for the Hightowers.

434
00:41:47.631 --> 00:41:49.299
Fuck the Hightowers.

435
00:41:55.097 --> 00:41:56.348
Keep walking.

436
00:42:00.644 --> 00:42:01.812
Don't make trouble.

437
00:42:10.446 --> 00:42:13.574
The White Worm said
you're one of Aegon's ratcatchers.

438
00:42:14.074 --> 00:42:15.451
You must be busy.

439
00:42:15.534 --> 00:42:17.703
That castle positively
crawls with them now.

440
00:42:19.121 --> 00:42:21.081
I heard the White Worm were dead.

441
00:42:21.165 --> 00:42:24.209
Her ghost told me
you were a betting man. Fighting pits?

442
00:42:24.293 --> 00:42:25.294
Dogs.

443
00:42:26.503 --> 00:42:27.921
And bones.

444
00:42:28.672 --> 00:42:29.965
How deep are your debts?

445
00:42:37.848 --> 00:42:41.560
I was also given to understand you possess
a unique knowledge of the Red Keep.

446
00:42:41.643 --> 00:42:43.061
Maegor's tunnels.

447
00:42:43.812 --> 00:42:45.481
Great big rat's nest. it is.

448
00:42:47.024 --> 00:42:49.693
I know them better
than the shape of my own cock.

449
00:42:52.738 --> 00:42:53.906
This is my friend.

450
00:42:55.115 --> 00:42:57.367
Tonight. he's going to be your friend.

451
00:42:58.535 --> 00:43:01.121
You're to find and slay
the Prince Aemond Targaryen.

452
00:43:02.915 --> 00:43:04.374
He has silver hair and one eye.

453
00:43:05.334 --> 00:43:06.919
He should be easy enough to find.

454
00:43:09.296 --> 00:43:11.089
But I understand
he's quite good in a fight.

455
00:43:11.173 --> 00:43:12.466
You'll want to take caution.

456
00:43:14.551 --> 00:43:17.638
That's one half.
You'll get the other when it's done.

457
00:43:29.942 --> 00:43:30.943
All right.

458
00:43:33.403 --> 00:43:35.197
But what if we can't find him?

459
00:43:39.743 --> 00:43:43.288
We've wasted precious days
in this war of quills and ravens.

460
00:43:43.372 --> 00:43:45.082
Words are wind.

461
00:43:46.208 --> 00:43:48.460
You should be leading the van.

462
00:43:48.544 --> 00:43:51.046
and I should be flying cover on Vhagar.

463
00:43:51.129 --> 00:43:53.966
No castle would dare to raise
Rhaenyra's banner against us.

464
00:43:54.842 --> 00:43:57.719
We would bring the whole of the Crownlands
to heel in weeks.

465
00:43:57.803 --> 00:43:59.888
Mayhaps we could petition the king.

466
00:44:00.681 --> 00:44:02.975
privately. to send us out.

467
00:44:05.394 --> 00:44:07.312
Rosby and Stokeworth.

468
00:44:07.396 --> 00:44:10.607
small castles
right in the shadow of King's Landing.

469
00:44:10.691 --> 00:44:14.403
- They would not want us for enemies.
- We could add their levies to our own...

470
00:44:15.821 --> 00:44:18.198
our host growing as we advance.

471
00:44:20.492 --> 00:44:22.286
Aye. it is a canny scheme.

472
00:44:23.370 --> 00:44:24.496
But moot.

473
00:44:25.122 --> 00:44:28.000
My brother is hostage
to my grandsire and mother.

474
00:44:28.083 --> 00:44:30.794
They tell him that a war of dragons
can yet be avoided.

475
00:44:31.712 --> 00:44:34.715
It is inevitable. They must see that.

476
00:44:34.798 --> 00:44:37.050
Otto fears to upset the order of things.

477
00:44:38.260 --> 00:44:40.095
And Alicent is simply...

478
00:44:41.763 --> 00:44:42.764
angry.

479
00:44:43.849 --> 00:44:47.144
- Angry?
- She blames me for starting this war.

480
00:44:47.227 --> 00:44:50.898
After she plotted with my father's council
to usurp his throne.

481
00:44:53.233 --> 00:44:56.403
Her Grace speaks with two tongues.

482
00:45:00.324 --> 00:45:01.783
She has a gentle heart.

483
00:45:03.076 --> 00:45:05.454
And Rhaenyra is a cunning spider.

484
00:45:06.246 --> 00:45:08.790
Long ago. she drew Alicent into her web.

485
00:45:10.167 --> 00:45:11.543
Intoxicated her.

486
00:45:13.587 --> 00:45:14.880
It is not your mother's fault.

487
00:45:17.049 --> 00:45:18.926
She holds love for our enemy.

488
00:45:21.094 --> 00:45:22.429
That makes her a fool.

489
00:45:39.655 --> 00:45:40.656
Lord Hand.

490
00:45:50.791 --> 00:45:54.670
Return to your post. Lord Commander.
I must have a word with the prince.

491
00:46:08.892 --> 00:46:10.686
It would concern me. grandson.

492
00:46:10.769 --> 00:46:15.899
if plans were being considered
beyond the ears of your king and his Hand.

493
00:46:16.525 --> 00:46:20.195
You've a zeal to act. I understand.
I was young once myself.

494
00:46:20.278 --> 00:46:22.781
I only wish to serve my king and my house.

495
00:46:29.287 --> 00:46:31.081
